The '''Niman''' were the double trinity of [[Deity/Legends|gods]] of the [[Kashi]] people. The [[Legions of Lettow]] named two [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] styles after the double trio: [[Form VI/Legends|Form VI: Niman]] and the dual blades technique [[Jar'Kai/Legends|Jar'Kai]]. Jar'Kai was called "Niman" because it used two blades, just as there were two trinities. Form VI was called Niman because the two trinities made up a total of six gods.<ref name="dfs4">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20050526a|series=The Dark Forces Saga|text=Part 4: Of the Crudest Matter}}</ref>

